.TH "DMINIT" "1" "" "Version 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dminit \(en creates and initialises DMPACK databases
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]dminit\f[R] \-\-help
.PP
\f[B]dminit\f[R] \-\-version
.PP
\f[B]dminit\f[R] \-\-\f[B]type\f[R] \f[I]type\f[R]
\-\-\f[B]database\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R] [\-\-\f[B]force\f[R]]
[\-\-\f[B]sync\f[R]] [\-\-\f[B]transfer\f[R]] [\-\-\f[B]wal\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]dminit\f[R] utility program creates beat, image, log, and
observation databases.
No action is performed if the specified database already exists, unless
command\-line argument \f[CR]\-\-force\f[R] is passed.
.PP
A synchronisation table is required for observation and log
synchronisation with an RPC server.
The argument may be omitted if this functionality is not used.
.PP
Write\-Ahead Logging (WAL) should be enabled for databases with multiple
readers.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-\-database\f[R], \f[B]\-d\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R]
File path of the new SQLite database.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-force\f[R], \f[B]\-F\f[R]
Force creation of tables even if the database already exists.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-help\f[R], \f[B]\-h\f[R]
Print available command\-line arguments and quit.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-sync\f[R], \f[B]\-s\f[R]
Add synchronisation tables.
Enable for data synchronisation between client and server.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-transfer\f[R], \f[B]\-x\f[R]
Add transfers table to database if type is \f[CR]image\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-\-type\f[R], \f[B]\-t\f[R] [beat|image|log|observ]
Type of database, either beat, image, log, or observation.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-version\f[R], \f[B]\-v\f[R]
Print version information and quit.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-wal\f[R], \f[B]\-W\f[R]
Enable Write\-Ahead Logging.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
Database was created.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Failure.
Database creation failed.
.SH EXAMPLE
Create a beat database:
.IP
.EX
$ dminit \-t beat \-d beat.db \-W
.EE
.PP
Create a log database with remote synchronisation tables:
.IP
.EX
$ dminit \-t log \-d log.db \-s \-W
.EE
.PP
Create an observation database with remote synchronisation tables:
.IP
.EX
$ dminit \-t observ \-d observ.db \-s \-W
.EE
.PP
Create an image database with transfer table:
.IP
.EX
$ dminit \-t image \-d image.db \-x
.EE
